      <div class="section-title">Asset Classes</div>
      <div class="section-subtitle">Not all investments are the same. Here's what exists, what it does, and where it fits in your portfolio.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="content-body">
      <div class="table-wrap">
        <table class="compare-table">
          <thead>
            <tr><th>Asset</th><th>Risk</th><th>Potential Return</th><th>BSJ Relevance</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td>Cash / Savings</td><td>Very Low</td><td>1–3% p.a.</td><td>Emergency fund only</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Bonds / Fixed Income</td><td>Low–Medium</td><td>3–7% p.a.</td><td>IDR gov bonds available via Indodax</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Stocks / Equities</td><td>Medium–High</td><td>7–15% p.a.</td><td>MSTR, ETFs via Saxo/IBKR</td></tr>
            <tr><td>ETFs</td><td>Medium</td><td>7–12% p.a.</td><td>MSTY (yield-focused), index ETFs</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Cryptocurrency</td><td>Very High</td><td>-90% to +1000%</td><td>BTC, ETH, SOL via Binance/Indodax</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Angel Investment</td><td>Extreme</td><td>0x to 100x</td><td>High conviction only — illiquid</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-title">₿ Crypto — The BSJ Teacher Advantage</div>
        <div class="card-body">
          Crypto is high risk but has produced the highest returns of any asset class over the last decade. Bitcoin specifically has outperformed every other asset over 1, 3, 5, and 10 year periods. The key is <strong>position sizing</strong> — never put more in crypto than you can afford to lose entirely, but don't put so little that a 10x move doesn't change your life.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-title">📈 Yield-Generating Assets</div>
        <div class="card-body">
          Some assets pay you while you hold them. MSTY pays monthly distributions. Staking SOL or ETH on Binance generates ~5–8% APY. Government bonds pay fixed interest. These are the building blocks of passive income — the goal is to build a portfolio that pays you monthly without selling anything.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="highlight highlight-blue">
        <strong>Diversification reality:</strong> Owning 5 different cryptocurrencies is NOT diversification — they are all highly correlated. True diversification means holding assets that move independently: stocks, crypto, bonds, and real assets (property, gold) respond differently to economic events.
      </div>
    </div>
