      <div class="section-num">Module 03 of 07</div>
      <div class="section-title">Your Risk Profile</div>
      <div class="section-subtitle">Before you invest a single dollar, you need to know yourself as an investor. Answer honestly.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="content-body">

      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-title">🎯 The Three Questions</div>
        <div class="card-body">
          <p style="margin-bottom:12px"><strong>1. Time horizon:</strong> When will you need this money? If the answer is less than 3 years, keep it in cash or low-risk assets. If 5+ years, you can take more risk — time smooths volatility.</p>
          <p style="margin-bottom:12px"><strong>2. Income stability:</strong> BSJ employment is relatively stable. You have a fixed salary, no dependents on your investment income (yet), and low fixed costs in Jakarta. This means you can tolerate more risk than a freelancer or someone with high fixed expenses.</p>
          <p><strong>3. Emotional tolerance:</strong> Can you watch your portfolio drop 50% and not panic-sell? Bitcoin dropped 80% in 2018 and 65% in 2022 — people who held are wealthy. People who sold at the bottom locked in permanent losses.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="highlight highlight-gold">
        <strong>BSJ Teacher Profile (typical):</strong> Stable income, low living costs, 10–20 year horizon, moderate-to-high risk tolerance. This profile suits a portfolio weighted toward growth assets (crypto, equities) with some yield generation (MSTY, staking).
      </div>

      <div class="table-wrap">
        <table class="compare-table">
          <thead><tr><th>Profile</th><th>Suggested Allocation</th><th>Expected Volatility</th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td>Conservative</td><td>60% bonds/cash, 30% stocks, 10% crypto</td><td>Low — may trail inflation</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Moderate</td><td>40% stocks/ETFs, 30% crypto, 20% bonds, 10% cash</td><td>Medium — steady growth</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Aggressive</td><td>50% crypto, 30% stocks, 20% yield assets</td><td>High — significant swings</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Very Aggressive</td><td>70%+ crypto, 20% high-growth stocks, 10% cash</td><td>Very high — not for everyone</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="highlight highlight-blue">
        <strong>Important:</strong> Your risk profile is not fixed. It changes as your wealth grows, your income changes, and your goals shift. Review it annually.
      </div>
    </div>
