    </div>
    <div class="content-body">
      <div class="highlight highlight-gold">
        <strong>Note:</strong> Access to some platforms may require additional steps depending on your location. Check local regulations and platform availability before signing up.
      </div>

      <ul class="step-list">
        <li class="step-item">
          <div class="step-num">1</div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <div class="step-title">Create your account</div>
            <div class="step-desc">Go to binance.com. Click Register. Use your personal email — not your BSJ email. Choose a strong, unique password and store it in a password manager.</div>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="step-item">
          <div class="step-num">2</div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <div class="step-title">Complete KYC verification</div>
            <div class="step-desc">Binance requires identity verification (Know Your Customer). Submit your passport photo and a selfie. This takes 10–30 minutes. Use your British passport for the cleanest verification experience.</div>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="step-item">
          <div class="step-num">3</div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <div class="step-title">Enable 2FA (Google Authenticator)</div>
            <div class="step-desc">Download Google Authenticator on your phone. Go to Security → Two-Factor Authentication → Google Authenticator. Scan the QR code. Never disable this — it's your primary account protection.</div>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="step-item">
          <div class="step-num">4</div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <div class="step-title">Deposit funds</div>
            <div class="step-desc">The easiest method from Indonesia: buy USDT on Indodax with IDR, then transfer USDT to your Binance wallet. Alternatively, use a credit/debit card (higher fees). Avoid bank transfer directly — it's complex from Indonesia.</div>
