        <li class="step-item">
          <div class="step-num">5</div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <div class="step-title">Make your first purchase</div>
            <div class="step-desc">Go to Trade → Spot. Search BTC/USDT. Start with a small amount ($50–100) to learn the interface. Use a Limit order rather than Market order to control your entry price.</div>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="step-item">
          <div class="step-num">6</div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <div class="step-title">Set up Earn / Staking</div>
            <div class="step-desc">Go to Earn → Simple Earn. You can stake ETH (~3–4% APY) and SOL (~6–8% APY) directly on Binance. This generates passive income on holdings you plan to hold long-term anyway.</div>
          </div>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <div class="highlight highlight-red">
        <strong>Security rules:</strong> Never share your seed phrase or private keys with anyone. Binance staff will never ask for your password. Enable withdrawal whitelist — only your known wallet addresses can receive funds. Use the Binance app only on your personal devices.
      </div>
