    </div>
    <div class="content-body">
      <div class="highlight highlight-blue">
        <strong>Why Indodax?</strong> Indodax accepts IDR bank transfers directly, which makes it the easiest way to convert your rupiah salary into crypto. You can buy USDT on Indodax and transfer it to Binance for a wider range of assets and lower trading fees.
      </div>

      <ul class="step-list">
        <li class="step-item">
          <div class="step-num">1</div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <div class="step-title">Create your account</div>
            <div class="step-desc">Go to indodax.com. Register with your email. You will need your Indonesian KTP or passport for verification. The process takes 1–2 business days for approval.</div>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="step-item">
          <div class="step-num">2</div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <div class="step-title">Link your Indonesian bank account</div>
            <div class="step-desc">Go to Profile → Bank Account. Add your BCA, Mandiri, BNI, or other Indonesian bank. This is how you deposit IDR. Transfers are processed within a few hours during business hours.</div>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="step-item">
          <div class="step-num">3</div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <div class="step-title">Deposit IDR and buy USDT</div>
            <div class="step-desc">Transfer IDR from your bank to your Indodax account. Once confirmed, go to Markets → USDT/IDR and buy USDT. This is your stable base currency for moving funds to Binance.</div>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="step-item">
          <div class="step-num">4</div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <div class="step-title">Transfer USDT to Binance</div>
            <div class="step-desc">In Indodax, go to Withdraw → USDT. Enter your Binance USDT deposit address (found in Binance → Wallet → Deposit → USDT → TRC20 network). Always double-check the network — use TRC20 for lowest fees.</div>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="step-item">
          <div class="step-num">5</div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <div class="step-title">Government bonds (optional)</div>
            <div class="step-desc">Indodax also offers Indonesian government bonds (ORI, SBR). These are low-risk IDR-denominated instruments paying 5–7% annually. A useful home for any IDR you want to keep in Indonesia long-term.</div>
          </div>
        </li>
